CPU Check is a little utility that speaks or makes a noise when a task
has finished.

You might for example tell it to inform you when your computer had
finished printing a document so you could see how it has done or load 
more paper.

This is likely to become one of your most commonly used utilities.

CPU Check can be found in many PD libraries and BBSs. If you
can't find it then send Ł5 $10 or equivalent, together with an SAE and
disk or your email address to me, the @{"Programmer" LINK PROGRAMMER}.

